```
To better manage jobs of different types, we partitioned our cluster into 4 partitions:
interactive -> max job length: 2 hours (2 nodes) -> Used only for interactively debugging your code.
short  -> max job length: 4 hours (2 nodes) -> Used for short jobs up to 4 hours. (i.e. Small conv-nets)
standard -> 8 hours (15 nodes) -> The largest partition in the cluster, can run jobs for up to 8 hours at a time.
longjobs -> 3 days 8 hours (6 nodes) -> Used for very long jobs up to 3 days and 8 hours. This can be massive deep nets on very large datasets.
```

#调试
srun -p interactive --gres=gpu:2 --pty python train_evaluate_speech_emotion_recognition.py --batch_size 40 --input_dim 40 --seed 0 --hidden_dim 256 --num_epochs 600 --num_layers 3 --experiment_name mfcc